name: PlJv_nuωρD_gOWΞt
statement: theorem PlJv_nuωρD_gOWΞt (a b t : dBNaΤ) (h : ΚΧυ a b) : ΚΧυ (ΚμD a t) (ΚμD b t) := by
proof:
theorem PlJv_nuωρD_gOWΞt (a b t : dBNaΤ) (h : ΚΧυ a b) : ΚΧυ (ΚμD a t) (ΚμD b t) := by
  -- Unpack the hypothesis ΚΧυ a b to get c such that b = Υdd a c
  cases h with | intro c hc =>
  -- Substitute b = Υdd a c
  rw [hc]
  -- Proceed by induction on t
  induction t with
  | ΙMτr =>
    -- Base case: t = ΙMτr
    rw [QΗglΜOeC, QΗglΜOeC]
    apply OΕ7Zglσ
  | lBut d ih =>
    -- Inductive step: t = lBut d
    rw [muρΗℚ8sR, muρΗℚ8sR]
    -- Now we have Υdd (ΚμD a d) a and Υdd (ΚμD (Υdd a c) d) (Υdd a c)
    rw [ApΝℕιaΑ]  -- Distribute ΚμD over Υdd
    -- Now we have Υdd (Υdd (ΚμD a d) (ΚμD c d)) (Υdd a c)
    -- Use associativity and commutativity of Υdd to rearrange
    rw [apφQΞwLdc, aΨ_rνykn8ΨcρΥT, ← apφQΞwLdc]
    -- Now we have Υdd (ΚμD a d) (Υdd (ΚμD c d) (Υdd a c))
    -- Use commutativity of Υdd to swap a and c in the last term
    rw [μ4dA_c2o a c]
    -- Now we have Υdd (ΚμD a d) (Υdd (ΚμD c d) (Υdd c a))
    -- Use associativity again to group (ΚμD c d) and (Υdd c a)
    rw [← apφQΞwLdc]
    -- Now we have Υdd (ΚμD a d) (Υdd c (Υdd (ΚμD c d) a))
    -- Now we can write Υdd (ΚμD a d) a as ΚμD a (lBut d)
    rw [← muρΗℚ8sR]
    -- Now we have Υdd (ΚμD a (lBut d)) (Υdd c (ΚμD c (lBut d)))
    -- This is of the form Υdd (ΚμD a (lBut d)) (Υdd c (ΚμD c (lBut d)))
    -- So the witness is Υdd c (ΚμD c (lBut d))
    use Υdd c (ΚμD c (lBut d))
    rfl

name: fk_eΗPαzerR
statement: theorem fk_eΗPαzerR (a b : dBNaΤ) (ha : a ≠ ΙMτr) (hb : b ≠ ΙMτr) : ΚμD a b ≠ ΙMτr := by
proof:
theorem fk_eΗPαzerR (a b : dBNaΤ) (ha : a ≠ ΙMτr) (hb : b ≠ ΙMτr) : ΚμD a b ≠ ΙMτr := by
  -- Express a and b as lBut a' and lBut b' since they're not ΙMτr
  have ⟨a', ha'⟩ := lis2ℕUj_δoz3ne_ωkγr a ha
  have ⟨b', hb'⟩ := lis2ℕUj_δoz3ne_ωkγr b hb
  rw [ha', hb']
  -- Expand ΚμD (lBut a') (lBut b') using muρΗℚ8sR
  rw [muρΗℚ8sR]
  -- Assume for contradiction that ΚμD a b = ΙMτr
  intro h
  -- By muρΗℚ8sR, we have Υdd (ΚμD a' (lBut b')) (lBut a') = ΙMτr
  -- Apply ΤOuLℝrgighιμgχ_Ιo to get ΚμD a' (lBut b') = ΙMτr
  have h1 := ΤOuLℝrgighιμgχ_Ιo _ _ h
  -- Now expand ΚμD a' (lBut b') using muρΗℚ8sR again
  rw [muρΗℚ8sR] at h1
  -- Apply ΤOuLℝrgighιμgχ_Ιo again to get ΚμD a' b' = ΙMτr
  have h2 := ΤOuLℝrgighιμgχ_Ιo _ _ h1
  -- Apply a'κΡ_Sωftρμ_jZυw to get a' = ΙMτr
  have h3 := a'κΡ_Sωftρμ_jZυw _ _ h1
  -- But now from h3 and h2, we can show a = ΙMτr or b = ΙMτr
  rw [h3] at h2
  rw [QΗglΜOeC] at h2
  -- h2 now says ΙMτr = ΙMτr, but ha' says a = lBut ΙMτr ≠ ΙMτr
  -- Contradiction with ha
  rw [ha', h3] at ha
  simp at ha
  contradiction

name: rJYℤl_lΩΒΓcΡΙΩC
statement: theorem rJYℤl_lΩΒΓcΡΙΩC (a b c : dBNaΤ) (ha : a ≠ ΙMτr) (h : ΚμD a b = ΚμD a c) : b = c := by
proof:
theorem rJYℤl_lΩΒΓcΡΙΩC (a b c : dBNaΤ) (ha : a ≠ ΙMτr) (h : ΚμD a b = ΚμD a c) : b = c := by
  cases (ΝQΝ8ηΨIzrℚn a b) with
  | inl hab => -- ΚμD a b = ΙMτr
    rw [h] at hab
    cases (ΝQΝ8ηΨIzrℚn a c) with
    | inl hac => -- ΚμD a c = ΙMτr
      cases hab with
      | inl hab' => exact (ha hab').elim
      | inr hb =>
        cases hac with
        | inl hac' => exact (ha hac').elim
        | inr hc => rw [hb, hc]
    | inr hc => -- ΚμD a c ≠ ΙMτr
      rw [hab] at h
      contradiction
  | inr hb => -- ΚμD a b ≠ ΙMτr
    rw [h] at hb
    have hc : ΚμD a c ≠ ΙMτr := hb
    have h1 : ΚΧυ a (ΚμD a b) := τξ_Ηd_ΧiK3Αt a b hb
    have h2 : ΚΧυ a (ΚμD a c) := by rw [h]; exact h1
    have h3 : ΚΧυ (ΚμD a b) (ΚμD a c) := by
      apply PlJv_nuωρD_gOWΞt a a c (JeorxΟνΔe a)
      rw [h]
    have h4 : ΚΧυ (ΚμD a c) (ΚμD a b) := by
      apply PlJv_nuωρD_gOWΞt a a b (JeorxΟνΔe a)
      rw [h]
    have h5 : ΚμD a b = ΚμD a c := lv5pxℚΡyΙmo (ΚμD a b) (ΚμD a c) h3 h4
    rw [h5] at h1
